1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,604
Namaskar! Aaj hum Newton's Second Law of Motion samjhenge.

2
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:09,436
Iska famous formula hai F = ma.

3
00:00:09,600 --> 00:00:13,148
Yahan F ka matlab hai Force, yaani bal.

4
00:00:13,266 --> 00:00:17,174
m ka matlab hai Mass, yaani object ka vajan.

5
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:22,825
Aur a ka matlab hai Acceleration, yaani uski speed badhne ki dar.

6
00:00:25,933 --> 00:00:30,038
Chalo ek example dekhte hain. Maan lo yeh

7
00:00:30,138 --> 00:00:33,321
ek block hai jiska mass 'm' hai.

8
00:00:33,466 --> 00:00:37,783
Jab hum ispar thoda sa Force 'F' lagate hain,

9
00:00:37,883 --> 00:00:42,102
toh isme thodi si Acceleration 'a' aati hai.

10
00:00:44,266 --> 00:00:47,706
Lekin agar hum Force double kar dein,

11
00:00:47,806 --> 00:00:51,054
yaani '2F', toh dekho kya hota hai.

12
00:00:51,200 --> 00:00:54,363
Acceleration bhi double ho jaati hai!

13
00:00:54,463 --> 00:00:57,892
Force zyada, toh acceleration bhi zyada.

14
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:03,647
Ab socho, agar hum Force utna hi rakhein, lekin

15
00:01:03,747 --> 00:01:08,596
mass double, yaani '2m' kar dein... toh kya hoga?

16
00:01:08,733 --> 00:01:11,945
Dekho, acceleration aadhi ho gayi!

17
00:01:13,066 --> 00:01:18,046
Toh isse saabit hota hai: Force badhne se acceleration badhti

18
00:01:18,146 --> 00:01:22,542
hai, aur mass badhne se acceleration kam ho jaati hai.

19
00:01:22,666 --> 00:01:25,134
Yeh hi hai Newton's Second Law.

